# Complete Implementation

```cpp
#include <hexi/static_buffer.h>

template<size_t buffer_size = 1024>
struct BufferInfo {
    size_t capacity;
    size_t current_size;
    size_t free_space;
};

// 1. Get the total capacity of a static_buffer
template<typename T, size_t N>
size_t get_buffer_capacity(const hexi::static_buffer<T, N>& buffer) {
    return buffer.capacity();
}

// 2. Get the current readable data size
template<typename T, size_t N>
size_t get_buffer_size(const hexi::static_buffer<T, N>& buffer) {
    return buffer.size();
}

// 3. Get the available free space
template<typename T, size_t N>
size_t get_buffer_free_space(const hexi::static_buffer<T, N>& buffer) {
    return buffer.capacity() - buffer.size();
}

BufferInfo<> get_buffer_info(const hexi::static_buffer<std::byte, 1024>& buffer) {
    BufferInfo<> info;
    info.capacity = get_buffer_capacity(buffer);
    info.current_size = get_buffer_size(buffer);
    info.free_space = get_buffer_free_space(buffer);
    return info;
}
```

## Explanation:

1. **`get_buffer_capacity`**: Returns the total capacity of the buffer using the `capacity()` method from `static_buffer`.

2. **`get_buffer_size`**: Returns the current amount of readable data in the buffer using the `size()` method, which represents the difference between write and read positions.

3. **`get_buffer_free_space`**: Calculates the available free space by subtracting the current size from the total capacity.

4. **`get_buffer_info`**: Aggregates all three metrics into a `BufferInfo` structure by calling the three helper functions above.

All functions are implemented as templates to work with any `static_buffer` type and size, making them reusable across different buffer configurations.

