   - `read_ptr`: Pointer to the current read position (from `buffer.data()`)
   - `is_empty`: Boolean indicating whether the buffer has no readable data (from `buffer.empty()`)

These implementations leverage the standard buffer adaptor interface methods that are available for contiguous containers like `std::vector<std::byte>`.

